      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The concept of \"perfect markets\" is an academic ideal, not a reflection of how global trade actually functions with subsidies and unfair labor practices. When experts point to deadweight loss, they are describing the theoretical cost, but they often ignore the real-world costs of dependency on foreign powers. Therefore, calling tariffs \"necessary\" is not bias; it is acknowledging that national economic stability sometimes requires pragmatic policy over purely theoretical models.",
